findings.recommendation:
Normalise all flag tokens before the critical-path check. Collect all single-character flags from '-X' tokens and from combined '-XY' tokens, then check whether the set contains both 'r' and 'f' (in any combination). This is O(n) in tokens and handles all POSIX flag forms:

```rust
fn has_recursive_force(tokens: &[&str]) -> bool {
    let mut flags = std::collections::HashSet::new();
    for t in tokens.iter().skip(1) {
        if let Some(rest) = t.strip_prefix('-') {
            flags.extend(rest.chars());
        }
    }
    flags.contains(&'r') && flags.contains(&'f')
}
```

